	Amarjit claims   gold  New Delhi: India rsquo;s Amarjit Singh won gold in men rsquo;s triple jump at the Malaysian pre-Olympic championship in Kuala Lumpur.  Amarjit jumped 16.64m to win gold at the National Stadium in Bukit Jalil in the Malaysian capital, according to information received here on Sunday.  In men rsquo;s 110m hurdles, national record holder Krishna Mohan finished second with a timing of 14.02s. Host runner Robani Hassan won the event in 13.85s.     
	 Saurav wins  Chennai: Top seed Saurav Ghosal did short work of compatriot Ritwik Bhattacharya 7-11, 11-7, 11-7, 11-6 to win the Chennai Open squash championship here on Sunday.
  Saurav was tentative in the beginning before he found his grooves to come back from one game down and pocket the match in 40 minutes.  In women rsquo;s section, fifth-seeded Dipika Pallikal rsquo;s dream run was halted as she lost to fourth seed Annie Au of Hong Kong 3-9, 8-10, 8-10 in 44 minutes.    
	 India to host  New Delhi: India will host the inaugural commonwealth basketball championship in July 2010, the international basketball federation (Fiba) has announced.  Fiba president Bob Elphinston said, ldquo;the tournament, with top eight Asian teams, is going to be a wonderful opportunity for the Indian basketball to grow further. rdquo;  ldquo;With this championship tournament the Commonwealth nations will get a very good opportunity to improve their performance by competing with each other, rdquo; Elphinston added.  Besides India, England, Nigeria, Canada and New Zealand and eight Asian countries are the probable participants in the tournament to be held just before the Delhi Commonwealth Games scheduled in October that year.
                                                                                                                                                               
